titles.title: A resolution to designate the Federal building located at 300 4th Street, Northeast, in the District of Columbia, as the "Daniel Webster Senate Page Residence", and for other purposes.

vote.text: Resolution agreed to in Senate without amendment by Voice Vote.

bill.summary: 11/24/1993--Introduced. Designates the Federal building located at 300 4th Street, Northeast, Washington, D.C., as the Daniel Webster Senate Page Residence.
